UNIT CONVERTER APPLICATION (PYTHON)
PROJECT REPORT

Project Title: Unit Converter Application (Python) 
Submitted by: Sanskriti Tyagi
 Institution: Vellore Institute of Technology Bhopal
Year: 2025

INTRODUCTION 

The Unit Converter is a Python-based application designed to convert values across length, weight, and temperature units. It simplifies daily measurement tasks and showcases Python fundamentals including functions, loops, conditionals, and input handling.

PROBLEM STATEMENT

 People frequently need to convert measurement units accurately. Manual conversion is error-prone and time-consuming. The objective is to build a simple console-based tool that performs fast and accurate unit conversions.

The problem:
 A simple, user-friendly tool is needed to accurately convert values between common units without requiring manual calculation or external formulas. 

Goal: To develop a Python-based Unit Converter that covers commonly used unit categories and delivers accurate results instantly.

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS

 - Convert length units (m, cm, km, miles)
 - Convert weight units (g, kg, lb) 
- Convert temperature units (C, F, K) 
- User-friendly interactive menu
 - Input validation 
- Repeated usage without restarting
- Support conversion for Length (meter, centimeter, kilometer, mile, foot, inch) 
- Support conversion for Weight/Mass (gram, kilogram, pound, ounce) 
-  Support conversion for Temperature (Celsius, Fahrenheit, Kelvin) 
-  Interactive menu-driven interface 
-  Bidirectional conversion (e.g., meter ↔ feet) 
-  Input validation (numeric values only) 
-  Option to perform multiple conversions without restarting 
-  Clear display of results with proper unit labels

NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS 
- High accuracy 
- Fast performance 
- Easy maintainability
- User-friendly design
- Portability across systems
-No external dependencies (pure Python) 

SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE 
Input Layer  Conversion Engine  Output Layer User inputs data  conversion logic processes it  results are displayed.

1.	User Input Module 
 Accepts value and unit selection. 2
2.	. Conversion Engine 
 Applies conversion formulas using Python functions.
3.	 Result Display 
Shows converted result.
4.	Loop Controller 
 Allows user to repeat operations.

