DESIGN DECISIONS & RATIONALE:
 Chosen to be console-based for simplicity. Modular functions allow easy expansion. Error handling improves reliability
• Functions were used to group conversion logic, improving code readability.
 • If-else statements were used for simple decisionmaking
. • No database was used to keep the system lightweight
. • Loop structure allows continuous use without restarting the program













IMPLEMENTATION DETAILS
Python used with structured functional design. Conversion formulas implemented with accuracy

Core logic uses Python fundamentals: 
• Functions for each category
• Dictionary-based unit mapping 
• Temperature conversion formulas 
• Error handling using try-except 
• Input validation for numeric values 
